result.execSummary:
The defendant David Antwan Hinton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).
  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant David Antwan Hinton in court with attorney Andrew Michael Meetz.  Defendant David Antwan Hinton in custody.  Matthew G. Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties and defendant. Additional Statements by David S., Robin B., Michael T.
AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 6 YEARS, consecutive, credit for 146 DAYS time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 4 YEARS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS. 

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 8 YEARS, consecutive, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 3 YEARS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim.
-No unsupervised contact with J.P., D.H., or L.H.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with drug dealers or drug houses.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges including: supervision fees, and DNA & DV surcharges to be paid from 25% of prison funds during initial confinement, balance paid during Extended Supervision and collected by DOC, failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
-Provide DNA Sample.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. 
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
